Class List.AbstractList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • javaslang.collection.List.AbstractList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Component type of the List.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, IntFunction<T>, List<T>, Seq<T>, Stack<T>, Traversable<T>, TraversableOnce<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    List.Cons, List.Nil
    Enclosing interface:
    List<T>

    public abstract static class List.AbstractList<T>
extends Object
implements List<T>

    This class is needed because the interface List cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.

    See Allow default methods to override Object's methods.

    1.1.0
